From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keyur Maru <kd2maru@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 02:15:47 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] gallium/freedreno: fix GMEM bin layout for MSAA
 depth/stencil

Two bugs in the GMEM key/layout path, both of which hang or fault an a5xx
(Adreno 506) as soon as an MSAA depth/stencil buffer is used.

The fdl layout's cpp already includes the sample multiplier (fd5_layout.c
computes cpp = blocksize * nr_samples), so multiplying by pfb->samples when
filling in key->zsbuf_cpp double-counts samples.  For 4x MSAA Z24S8 that yields
cpp 64 instead of 16 -- a depth/stencil buffer that cannot fit GMEM even at the
minimum tile size, and a layout that overflows GMEM and resolves out of bounds
into a GPU write translation fault.  Use layout->cpp directly.

That over-large cpp also exposed the second bug: calc_nbins()'s search loop
increments nbins_x/nbins_y until layout_gmem() fits, with no bound.  Once both
dimensions are subdivided to the minimum tile size the bin dimensions -- and so
the per-bin GMEM footprint -- can no longer shrink, so if the layout still does
not fit the loop simply spins forever, hanging the render thread.  Bound the
search by the minimum achievable tile size and clamp to the smallest layout,
warning once, instead of never terminating.
---
 .../drivers/freedreno/freedreno_gmem.c        | 35 +++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 33 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/gallium/drivers/freedreno/freedreno_gmem.c b/src/gallium/drivers/freedreno/freedreno_gmem.c
index 9f7124d..9497fd9 100644
--- a/src/gallium/drivers/freedreno/freedreno_gmem.c
+++ b/src/gallium/drivers/freedreno/freedreno_gmem.c
@@ -232,12 +232,36 @@ calc_nbins(struct gmem_key *key, struct fd_gmem_stateobj *gmem)
    /* then find a bin width/height that satisfies the memory
     * constraints:
     */
+   /* channel A17: bound the search.  Once both dimensions are subdivided down
+    * to the minimum tile size, bin_w/bin_h (and thus per-bin GMEM use) can no
+    * longer shrink, so if layout_gmem() still doesn't fit, incrementing nbins
+    * forever is a pure infinite loop (observed hanging the render thread when
+    * the reported GMEM size is too small for a given cbuf/zsbuf cpp).  Clamp to
+    * the smallest achievable layout instead of spinning. */
+   uint32_t max_nbins_x = DIV_ROUND_UP(key->width, screen->info->tile_align_w);
+   uint32_t max_nbins_y = DIV_ROUND_UP(key->height, screen->info->tile_align_h);
    while (!layout_gmem(key, nbins_x, nbins_y, gmem)) {
       if (nbins_y > nbins_x) {
          nbins_x++;
       } else {
          nbins_y++;
       }
+      if ((nbins_x >= max_nbins_x) && (nbins_y >= max_nbins_y)) {
+         nbins_x = MAX2(1, max_nbins_x);
+         nbins_y = MAX2(1, max_nbins_y);
+         static bool warned = false;
+         if (!warned) {
+            warned = true;
+            mesa_logw("fd_gmem: layout did not converge (gmemsize=0x%x "
+                      "%ux%u cbuf0_cpp=%u zs_cpp=%u tile_align=%ux%u) - "
+                      "clamping to %ux%u bins",
+                      screen->gmemsize_bytes, key->width, key->height,
+                      key->cbuf_cpp[0], key->zsbuf_cpp[0],
+                      screen->info->tile_align_w, screen->info->tile_align_h,
+                      nbins_x, nbins_y);
+         }
+         break;
+      }
    }
 
    /* Lets see if we can tweak the layout a bit and come up with
@@ -462,9 +486,16 @@ gmem_key_init(struct fd_batch *batch, bool assume_zs, bool no_scis_opt)
 
    if (has_zs || assume_zs) {
       struct fd_resource *rsc = fd_resource(pfb->zsbuf.texture);
-      key->zsbuf_cpp[0] = rsc->layout.cpp * pfb->samples;
+      /* channel A17: fdl layout->cpp ALREADY includes the MSAA sample
+       * multiplier (fd5_layout.c: cpp = blocksize * nr_samples), so multiplying
+       * by pfb->samples here double-counts samples.  For 4x MSAA Z24S8 that
+       * yields cpp=64 instead of 16, which cannot fit GMEM even at the minimum
+       * tile size -> the calc_nbins() search never converges (infinite loop) and
+       * the resulting layout overflows GMEM (out-of-bounds resolve -> GPU write
+       * translation fault).  Use layout->cpp directly, matching upstream Mesa. */
+      key->zsbuf_cpp[0] = rsc->layout.cpp;
       if (rsc->stencil)
-         key->zsbuf_cpp[1] = rsc->stencil->layout.cpp * pfb->samples;
+         key->zsbuf_cpp[1] = rsc->stencil->layout.cpp;
 
       /* If we clear z or s but not both, and we are using z24s8 (ie.
        * !separate_stencil) then we need to restore the other, even if
